# Proxy-router SDK workflow (no fork)

NodeNeo embeds `github.com/MorpheusAIs/Morpheus-Lumerin-Node/proxy-router` as
its on-chain SDK. **The absgrafx fork is retired.** The local sibling checkout
at `../Morpheus-Lumerin-Node` now tracks the upstream community repo directly
on the `dev` branch.

## Repo map

| Path | Remote | Default branch | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `/Volumes/moon/repo/personal_mor/nodeneo` | `absgrafx/nodeneo` (ours) | `dev` | App + Go gateway. Push freely. |
| `/Volumes/moon/repo/personal_mor/Morpheus-Lumerin-Node` | `MorpheusAIs/Morpheus-Lumerin-Node` (upstream) | `dev` (promotes to `main`) | **Not our fork.** PR-only. |

## SDK consumption — three modes

`nodeneo/go/go.mod` decides where the SDK comes from:

1. **Pinned (release / quiet periods)** — no `replace` directive; depend on a
   pseudo-version cut from upstream `dev`:
   ```
   go get github.com/MorpheusAIs/Morpheus-Lumerin-Node/proxy-router@<dev-commit>
   go mod tidy
   ```
2. **Local iteration (active SDK work)** — keep the `replace` pointing at the
   sibling checkout while iterating; this is the current state:
   ```
   replace github.com/MorpheusAIs/Morpheus-Lumerin-Node/proxy-router => ../../Morpheus-Lumerin-Node/proxy-router
   ```
3. **Promotion to `main`** — once upstream promotes `dev` → `main`, switch the
   pseudo-version to a `main` commit. Do **not** silently switch branches.

When you finish an SDK change, always end on mode 1 (pinned) before tagging a
NodeNeo release. Mode 2 must never appear in a tagged build.

## When you need to change the SDK (`proxy-router/mobile/...`)

Don't push to `dev` or `main` upstream — ever. Use a feature branch + PR.

```bash
cd /Volumes/moon/repo/personal_mor/Morpheus-Lumerin-Node
git fetch origin
git checkout -b mobile/<short-feature> origin/dev
# ...edit proxy-router/mobile/... and run tests in BOTH repos...
git push -u origin mobile/<short-feature>
gh pr create --base dev --repo MorpheusAIs/Morpheus-Lumerin-Node \
  --title "feat(proxy-router/mobile): <what>" \
  --body  "<why + testing notes>"
```

Branch naming follows existing upstream conventions: `mobile/<feature>`,
`bugfix/<topic>`, `docs/<topic>`, `cicd/<topic>`. Look at `git branch -r` for
prior art before inventing a new prefix.

After the PR merges to `dev`:

```bash
cd /Volumes/moon/repo/personal_mor/nodeneo/go
# remove the local replace, then:
go get github.com/MorpheusAIs/Morpheus-Lumerin-Node/proxy-router@<merged-commit>
go mod tidy
go test ./...
```

Commit the `go.mod`/`go.sum` bump in NodeNeo as a follow-up.

## Hard rules

- **Never** `git push origin dev` or `git push origin main` in
  `Morpheus-Lumerin-Node`. Always go through a PR against `dev`.
- **Never** force-push to any upstream branch.
- **Never** reintroduce `github.com/absgrafx/Morpheus-Lumerin-Node/...` as a
  module path or replace target — the fork is dead.
- Run `go test ./...` and `go vet ./...` in **both** repos before opening the PR.
- Three redaction surfaces stay in lockstep — if you touch one, touch all three:
  - `Morpheus-Lumerin-Node/proxy-router/mobile/redact.go`
  - `nodeneo/go/internal/gateway/redact.go`
  - `nodeneo/lib/utils/error_redaction.dart`

## `proxy-router/mobile/` post-split layout

The SDK was split by concern. Match the existing file when adding to it:

| File | Concern |
|---|---|
| `sdk.go` | `SDK` struct, `NewSDK`, lifecycle, version strings |
| `sdk_chat.go` | `SendPrompt*`, `SendChatCompletion`, `SendEmbeddings`, reasoning extraction |
| `sdk_sessions.go` | Open/Close/Get session(s) |
| `sdk_models.go` | Model cache, ratings, stake estimate |
| `sdk_wallet.go` | Wallet ops, balances, ETH/MOR transfers |
| `sdk_maintenance.go` | Background session maintenance loop |
| `sdk_helpers.go` | Shared helpers (JSON, big.Int formatting, URL parsing) |
| `redact.go` | Provider-endpoint redaction at the SDK boundary |
| `attestation_config.go` | TEE / sigstore config knobs |
| `httpserver.go` | Optional embedded proxy-router HTTP server |
| `storage.go` | In-memory KV used by mobile builds |
| `types.go` | Public DTOs (`Session`, `Balance`, ...) |
